I fully agree  "Worries rise about co-opting of religion" (March 19). Christian nationalism poses a grave danger to our democracy. I did get a laugh, though, when I read the comment by Southern Baptist leader Russell Moore describing Christian nationalism as "heretical." I was reminded of the great Emo Philips joke where Emo is trying to pin down the religion of someone he encounters on a walk. It ends with this exchange: " 'Northern Conservative Baptist Great Lakes Region Council of 1879, or Northern Conservative Baptist Great Lakes Region Council of 1912?' He said, 'Northern Conservative Baptist Great Lakes Region Council of 1912.' I said, 'Die, heretic!' " You've read your complimentary articles for this time period.
